**Analyzing `opt`'s Log**: The log shows the SLP vectorizer is attempting to
vectorize a bundle containing four phi nodes that originate from different
binary operations: `%shl = shl i32 0, 1`, `%mul = mul i32 0, 0`, `%add = add
i32 0, 0`, and `%add1 = add i32 0, 1`. The crash occurs when trying to process
the `%add = add i32 0, 0` instruction as part of building operands for
vectorization.\n\n3. **Root Cause Analysis**: From the debugger output, we can
see:\n   - `FromOpcode = 25` (shl)\n   - `ToOpcode = 13` (add)\n   -
`FromCIValue = APInt(32b, 1u)` (value 1)\n   \n   The issue is in the `Shl`
case handling in `getOperand()`. When converting from `shl` to something other
than `mul`, the code assumes that the shift amount must be zero (so the result
is just the original value). However, in our case, we have `shl i32 0, 1` where
the shift amount is 1, but since the first operand is 0, the result is still 0.
The current logic only checks if `FromCIValue.isZero()` but doesn't account for
the fact that when the non-constant operand of the shift is zero, any shift
amount will produce zero.\n   \n   The `isBinOpWithConstantInt()` function
identifies which operand is the constant. In `shl i32 0, 1`, the constant is
