to `add`, and the shift amount is non-zero, this conversion should not be
attempted in the first place.\n   + The proper fix is to strengthen the
condition in the `Shl` case to also allow the conversion when the non-constant
operand is zero. We can check if the other operand (LHS) is a constant zero or
can be determined to be zero through analysis.\n\n   Actually, examining the
code more carefully, the issue is that the current logic assumes that for `shl`
to be convertible to non-`mul` operations, the shift amount must be zero. But
when the value being shifted is zero, any shift amount produces zero, which is
